<p>July 10th, 2011, late afternoon<br />
Shark Bay, Western Australia<br /><br />
These are modern examples of perhaps one of the earliest lifeforms on Earth: Stromatolites. They grow in shallow, hypersaline waters in Shark Bay. This photo was taken from an observation platform which extended out over the 'reef'.
